      • hideTransitiveEdges

        public void hideTransitiveEdges​(org.eclipse.sirius.diagram.DSemanticDiagram diagram,
                                boolean excludeCyclicalDependencies)
        Hides all edges in the diagram that are transitive. An edge is considered transitive if there exists another path from its source to its target
        Parameters:
        diagram - the MRS diagram
        excludeCyclicalDependencies - if true, then edges that are part of cycles will not be hidden regardless of their being transitive or not
